snippet.title: Lenovo Ideapad 320 - Unboxing & Review
snippet.description:
Lenovo Ideapad 320 - Unboxing & Review

Lenovo 320-15IKB, Intel Core i5 7200U 2,50 GHz, Core 2, 8 GB, 15,6" 1920x1080, SSD 256 GB, Free DOS, NVIDIA GeForce 940MX (4 GB), DVD±RW, 1x 10/100/1000, 802.11ac, BT 4.1, HDMI 1, USB 3.0 2, USB Type-C 1, 2,2 kg

The machine is powered by a Kaby Lake processor. The GeForce graphics solution, at least to some degree, allows for the use of video games. 

Powered by 7th Gen Intel® Core™ i7 processing, up to NVIDIA GeForce 940MX graphics and startling FHD clarity, the Ideapad 320 is designed to meet your productivity and entertainment needs.

The IdeaPad 320 offers up to Full High Definition resolution, and features anti-glare technology. You'll enjoy true visual clarity when you watch movies, browse the web, and more.

The laptop comes equipped with two USB Type-A ports (USB 3.1 Gen 1) and one USB Type-C port (USB 3.1 Gen 1), which are accompanied by one HDMI Out port and a gigabit Ethernet port.

Gaming Performance
The hardware of the IdeaPad allows most computer games to run smoothly at HD resolution (1366x768) at the medium quality settings.
